  "texts": [
    "A structure-based residual neural network (MutCompu-teX) is subsequently developed and used to generate activity-enriched variants of a plant methyltransferase, which are rapidly screened with the biosensor.",
    "Functional enzyme variants are identified that yield a 60% improvement in product titer, 2-fold higher catalytic activity, and 3-fold lower off-product regioisomer formation.",
    "A solved crystal structure elucidates the mechanism behind key beneficial mutations.",
    "Alkaloids produced by the Amaryllidoideae subfamily of flowering plants have great therapeutic promise, including anticancer, fungicidal, antiviral, and acetylcholinesterase inhibition properties.",
    "Among the approximate ~600 reported Amaryllidoideae alkaloids (AAs), those derived from the lycorine, haemanthamine, and narciclasine scaffolds have been used as lead molecules in anticancer research [1] [2] [3] [4]."
  ]
}